features: POWERFUL TRACKER - Tile helps you keep track of your things. The Tile Pro streamlined shape hangs great on keys, bags or luggage. Use our free app to find them.
FIND NEARBY -- Use the Tile app to ring your Tile when it’s within Bluetooth range, or ask your Smart Home device to find it for you.
FIND FAR AWAY -- When outside of Bluetooth range, use the Tile app to view your Tile’s most recent location on a map.
FIND YOUR PHONE- Double press the button on your Tile to make your phone ring, even when it’s on silent.

NOTIFY WHEN FOUND -- Enlist the secure and anonymous help of the Tile Network to help find your things. If your lost Tile is found, If your Tile is lost, add your contact information so you can be reached when someone scans the QR code on your lost Tile.
ANDROID, IOS & SMART HOME COMPATIBLE - Find your things with the free Tile app on both iOS and Android devices. Tile also works with Amazon Alexa, Hey Google and Siri
TECH SPECS: Water-Resistant (IP67 rated), Up to 1-year replaceable battery, Up to 400 ft / 120 m Bluetooth range
UPGRADE TO A PREMIUM PLAN: Get proactive Smart Alert notifications when you leave something behind, and with Item Reimbursement, if we can’t find your Tiled item, we reimburse you.
body.description: Tile Pro is a powerful tracker for keys, backpacks, and purses. Water-resistant with an up to 400 ft. Bluetooth range, our loudest ring and up to 1-year replaceable battery, Pro easily attaches to anything you need to keep track of regularly. Just open the free Tile app and tap Find to locate your stuff. You can also double press the button on your Pro to ring and find your phone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Should have gotten one sooner
reviews.reviewText: I'm not sure how durable a device this is, it seems a bit flimsy, but if it fails after less than a year I think I still got my money's worth. It's helped me keep track of my phone and my keys - if I misplace either one, I trigger it from the other, either the app on my phone or the button on the tile on my keychain. To get the most from it you should pair it with a smartphone on an active contract, leave Bluetooth on and battery saver off. If the phone isn't on contract you'll still get some functionality, or you can get extra features from Tile if you sign up, but it's pretty useful right out of the box.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Keep Track of Your Belongings with the Tile Performance Pack!
reviews.reviewText: Are you tired of searching high and low for your keys, wallet, and other important items? Say goodbye to the endless frustration with the Tile Performance Pack. This powerful 2-pack includes one Tile Pro and one Tile Slim, ensuring that you can easily find all your things, no matter how elusive they may be.The Tile Pro and Tile Slim are your trusty sidekicks in the battle against misplaced belongings. Attach them to your keys, slip them into your wallet, or stick them to any item you want to keep track of. With their help, you'll never have to tear your house apart in search of your essentials again.When your belongings decide to play hide-and-seek, simply use the Tile app to ring your Tile when it's within Bluetooth range. It's like having your very own personal assistant calling out to your lost items. And if you're feeling extra lazy, you can even ask your Smart Home device to find your Tile for you. It's like having a search party at your command.But what if your belongings are playing a game of "hide-and-go-far"? Don't worry, the Tile app has you covered. Even when your Tile is outside of Bluetooth range, you can still view its most recent location on a map. It's like having a GPS tracker for your cherished possessions.Oh, and let's not forget about your phone! We've all experienced the panic of misplacing our phones, especially when they're on silent mode. With the Tile Performance Pack, you can simply double press the button on your Tile to make your phone ring, even in its sneaky silent state. It's like having a magician summon your phone from thin air.And here's a little joke for you: Why did the Tile throw a party? Because it found its missing keys and wanted to celebrate with a rousing round of "Key-sa Nova"! It's all fun and games when you have the Tile Performance Pack on your side.The Tile Performance Pack is compatible with both iOS and Android devices, so no matter what type of phone you have, you can enjoy the benefits of Tile. Plus, it works seamlessly with popular smart home devices like Amazon Alexa, Hey Google, and Siri. Your virtual assistants will be on high alert, ready to assist you in your quest to find your misplaced items.With water-resistant designs, long battery life, and impressive Bluetooth ranges, the Tile Pro and Tile Slim are the ultimate companions for your daily adventures. And if you want to take your tracking game to the next level, you can upgrade to a premium plan. Get proactive Smart Alert notifications and even enjoy item reimbursement if your Tile goes missing. It's like having a personal search and rescue team.So, why continue the frustrating game of hide-and-seek with your belongings when you can have the Tile Performance Pack on your side? With its powerful trackers and convenient features, you'll never have to utter those dreaded words, "Has anyone seen my...?" again. Get your Tile Performance Pack today and let the treasure hunt begin!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very useful gadget
reviews.reviewText: Being able to track your luggage when you travel is a really useful feature especially since airlines seem to be really casual about reuniting you with it again.I opted for thus modek because it has replaceable batteries which means that it should rebain useful for some time.I don't travel constantly so when I'm not travelling, I hide it in my car. So it makes for a very descrete tracking device in case my car gets stolen or to easily locate it in a car park.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy set up, easy to use.
reviews.reviewText: This tracker set up easy and fast using the Tile app. I used it successfully several times to find my phone, even so much that the alert tune was stuck in my head! I liked it so well I bought one for my mom. I rated it down one star because while demonstrating how it works for my mom, it did not work. I pushed the button twice on the tile but my phone didn't sound the alert. I just turned off my bluetooth on my phone then turned it on again and that fixed it. I love the security of being able to find my phone with my tile, or find my keys with my phone, especially if I'm running late for work.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I am not impressed with the tile network. Often, it an not locate the tiles even within 5 feet of your phone. I've spent a lot of time on this, trying to get the tiles to ring and for the phone to ring when you press the tile's button. I replaced the batteries which are CR2032. I also ordered the The Wallet. That thing constantly rings your phone when you put it in your wallet and sit, but rarely works when you try to find it.Bad tech. Waste of money. I'm currently trying other alternatives.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Much louder than Apple Air Tags!
reviews.reviewText: I got so tired of my nieces and nephews losing things and having to turn everything off to try to hear those Apple Air Tags that wouldn't even wake up a newborn baby. I have used Tile products for years in my purse, wallet, keys, luggage, etc. I decided to just give these to my family and they even have to admit that these are loud and do the job wonderfully. You can hear a Tile and just follow the sound from downstairs or another room. I know from experience. The Tile app shows the location so you know if you left something at the airport or a house or anywhere. You can even connect with other Tile users nearby to find things. They've really improved it over the years so I remain a faithful customer.
